  "texts": [
    "SVC is valued for its adaptability and efficacy in handling the complex, highdimensional spaces typical of text data, while Gaussian Naive Bayes, appreciated for its straightforwardness and rapid processing, was also tested.",
    "Our optimal SVC model was finely tuned to a C value of 214.3, with gamma set to 0.0005, and utilized a linear kernel.",
    "These parameters, chosen via Bayesian optimization, were carefully calibrated to improve the model's capacity to accurately separate classes without sacrificing the ability to generalize.",
    "The linear kernel selection aimed to exploit the textual data's intrinsic high dimensionality without unnecessarily complicating the model.",
    "For GaussianNB, the variance smoothing parameter was set to 0.1, a decision aimed at bolstering model robustness by fine-tuning the variance in feature likelihood, thereby enhancing prediction consistency across diverse datasets."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}